<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-22-1396 </DOCNO><TEXT>This chapter provides an understanding of the basic techniques of recombinantDNA research. As obtaining a product is an important industrial consideration,the strategies and problems involved in getting recombinant DNAs to beexpressed are discussed. Finally a relatively new area for research inwhich specific enzymes may be engineered for use in the biotechnologyindustry is explored. (Refs. 44).</TEXT></DOC>